body_html:
@gunan I see, thank you.

But anyway the solution by @hajome73 doesn't seem to be ideal.
I took a closer look at the output after applying the solution and it looks suspicious to me. See this gist: https://gist.github.com/trd714/551cd37e00a57a83ae40a36f195b470b.
Firstly, I see two lines that say "Creating TensorFlow device" (27 and 32).
Secondly, I get "Out of range" at line 33. After reading the line number 34 I assume that it's somehow related to the CPU as it states _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0". Are lines 33 and 34 an issue at all? If yes, are they related to the initial issue or should I create a new one?

P.S. I had to wrap the last statement at https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/get_started#basic_usage (estimator.evaluate(input_fn=input_fn)) in a print() function to get the output.

@gunan I see, thank you.

But anyway the solution by @hajome73 doesn't seem to be ideal.
I took a closer look at the output after applying the solution and it looks suspicious to me. See this gist: https://gist.github.com/trd714/551cd37e00a57a83ae40a36f195b470b.
Firstly, I see two lines that say "Creating TensorFlow device" (27 and 32).
Secondly, I get "Out of range" at line 33. After reading the line number 34 I assume that it's somehow related to the CPU as it states _device="/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/cpu:0". Are lines 33 and 34 an issue at all? If yes, are they related to the initial issue or should I create a new one?

P.S. I had to wrap the last statement at https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/get_started#basic_usage (estimator.evaluate(input_fn=input_fn)) in a print() function to get the output.
